League Photos  Images from the African American social service, research, and advocacy organization.  CITY 2000 More than 14,000 images from the Comer Archive of Chicago in the Year 2000.  Congressman Frank Annunzio Photo Collection Images of Frank Annunzio who represented Chicago for 28 years in the U.S. House of Representatives.  Cook County Forest Preserve Collections More than 3,000 photographs, blueprints and documents digitized from the Library’s extensive archive of the Forest Preserve District of Cook County. You can also browse the collections separately by:  Photographs  Blueprints  Documents  C. William Brubaker Collection Chicago architecture in photographs and drawings from the mid-20th century. Hull-House Yearbook Photographic Collection  Images of Hull House from 1906-1941. IDOT Chicago Traffic Photographs Mid-20th century street scenes from the Illinois Department of Transportation. Metropolitan Planning Council, 1934-2000 Images related to low-income housing and neighborhood development in Chicago. Picture Chicago Images of Chicago from digitized books. Puerto Rican Cultural Center Collection More than 400 photographs, flyers, posters and documents from Chicago’s Juan Antonio Corretjer Puerto Rican Cultural Center. Remembering Richard J. Daley Learn about Richard J. Daley’s administration through photographs, audio and video interviews and documents. Richard J. Daley Era Photographs Seven Settlement Houses: Database of Photographs  More than 800 photographs from Henry Booth House, the Hyde Park Neighborhood Club, the Marcy-Newberry Association and other settlement houses in Chicago. Society of Typographic Arts Exhibition catalogs and documents from this Chicago professional association for graphic designers. The Circle Campus: A look back through 50 years  Hundreds of images of the campus design, construction and early campus life. The Circle Yearbooks Digitized Circle Campus Yearbooks between 1966 and 1972. College of Medicine Class Photos Yearbook images from the 1880s to the early 1900s. Gallery 400 Collection Over 2,500 images from the non-profit arts center on the UIC campus. The Image of Research Images from the yearly competition of UIC graduate student research projects. University of Illinois at Navy Pier Photographs (1945-1948) More than 400 photographs of the Navy Pier campus in the 1940s. University campus stock photos Images of the UIC Campus available for purchase from UIC Photo Services. Medical images  Chicago Area Pharmacy Photographs Taken in 1955  College of Medicine Class Photos Yearbook images from the 1880s to the early 1900s.  Embellished Medical Title Pages: The 16th through 18th Centuries  Florence Nightingale Letters  Illinois Training School for Nurses 200 images of the nursing school and of Cook County Hospital between 1883 and 1929.  Percival Bailey Brain Specimens More than 200 images of plastic-embedded normal and pathological brain specimens.  Other images from the Library’s collections  H. D. Carberry Caribbean Studies Collection More than 500 digitized book jackets from the Library’s outstanding collection of Caribbean literature.  Sheet music collection  Nearly 2,000 images of sheet music covers from the late 19th and early 20th century.  Sierra Leone Documents and Images, 1792-1825  Digitized documents from the Library’s Sierra Leone collection.      Collections  Back to content     Articles    Books & Media    Digital Images     UIC Image Collections      Special Collections & University Archives    Maps & GIS    Theses, Dissertations & UIC Publications               Logo for the University of Illinois at Chicago       University  Library          Locations           Richard J. Daley Library    801 S. Morgan   Chicago , IL  60607       Circulation  (312) 996-2724    Reference  (312) 996-2726    Special Collections & University Archives  (312) 996-2742    Course Reserves  (312) 996-2719                             Library of the Health Sciences-Chicago    1750 W. Polk St.   